asmtest provides a static library, headers and a pkg-config file.

    With CMake, link the static library directly:

        find_path(ASMTEST_INCLUDE_DIR NAMES asmtest.h PATH_SUFFIXES asmtest)
        find_library(ASMTEST_LIBRARY NAMES asmtest)
        target_include_directories(main PRIVATE ${ASMTEST_INCLUDE_DIR})
        target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE ${ASMTEST_LIBRARY})

    Or via pkg-config (installed to lib/pkgconfig/asmtest.pc):

        pkg_check_modules(ASMTEST REQUIRED IMPORTED_TARGET asmtest)
        target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE PkgConfig::ASMTEST)

Note: libasmtest.a provides main() (the test runner); a consumer supplies
TEST() cases via #include <asmtest.h>.
